              <p class="MsoListParagraph"><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="line-height: 18px;">With certain exceptions, California law requires that: (1) employers provide hourly employees with at least a 30-minute uninterrupted meal break every day in which the employee works more than 5 hours; and (2) employers provide employees who work more than 10 hours in one day with two 30-minute uninterrupted meal breaks.</span></span>
